itemDescription: English nurse; former Matron-in-Chief of the Queen Alexandra's Royal Naval Nursing Service

wikipedia_page.main: Dame Doris Winifred Beale,  (9 August 1889 – 14 January 1971) was a British military nurse and nursing administrator who served as Matron-in-Chief of Queen Alexandra's Royal Naval Nursing Service from 1941 to 1944 during the Second World War. In the 1944 Birthday Honours she was appointed Dame Commander of the Order of the British Empire (DBE), a first in the Royal Naval Nursing Service.
